IRS990.Desc: RESTORATION, RECONSTRUCTION, MAINTENANCE AND INTERPRETATION OF AN HISTORIC FARM TO DEMONSTATE THE RURAL LIFESTYLE OF 18TH AND 19TH CENTURY MORAVIAN COMMUNITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAINTAINS A RESTORED HISTORIC FARM WHICH DEMONSTRATES THE RURAL LIFESTYLE OF 18TH AND 19TH CENTURY MORAVIANS FOR PUBLIC EXHIBITION.

THE ENDOWMENT ASSETS ATTEMPT TO PROVIDE A PREDICTABLE STREAM OF FUNDING TO PROGRAMS SUPPORTED BY ITS ENDOWMENT FUNDS WHILE ALSO MAINTAINING THE PURCHASING POWER OF THOSE ENDOWMENT ASSETS OVER THE LONG-TERM. A SPENDING POLICY IS DETERMINED ANNUALLY BY THE INVESTMENT COMMITTEE.
THERE WERE NO UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS IDENTIFIED OR LIABILITIES RECORDED FOR THE FISCAL YEAR ENDED FEBRUARY 28, 2018.
HISTORICAL AND MUSEUM OBJECTS DONATED TO THE ORGANIZATIONS ARE NOT REFLECTED ON THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. ANY COLLECTIONS ACQUIRED BY PURCHASE ARE EXPENSED IN THE YEAR PURCHASED.
